summary: Hello, hope everyone is having a great summer! The temperature is a bit too high for liking, but it won’t stop me from working...
caption:
Hello, hope everyone is having a great summer! The temperature is a bit too high for liking, but it won’t stop me from working >:3
okay now on to the drawing:
Despite they finished their cup of coffee, Mahsira still fall asleep in the road trip. They are gonna miss the beautiful sun rise xP. This is a little practice I did from last week, did the whole drawing with one layer, I didn’t realized that until I finished ^^;.
I also have a second drawing to share today! I drew Mahsira is hanging out with the new Pokémon Wooloo, I knew I have to draw it after I saw how fluffy it is xD.

summary: You are on your last pokemon, beaten, defeated, your low level wooloo badly hurt as a iron tail has crushed her against you, and...
body:
You are on your last pokemon, beaten, defeated, your low level wooloo badly hurt as a iron tail has crushed her against you, and the both of you against a wall.

You can feel your bones break, but you can also hear your Wooloo anguished cries, so in a last act of defiance you crawl between your Sheep and your opponent, your body a shield, as the big, bad evil Local Team Boss laughs, his Giant Pokemon ready to strike you to and your sheep to pulp.

Tears come to your eyes but you stand your ground, ready to give your life for your little sheep, as the enemy pokemon open it’s maws to obliterate you in one, single hyperbeam…

But your sheep will not have it. She wants to help you as much as you want to defend her, overcoming her usually cowardly nature to save the person that believed in her, so, with a wobbly jump he goes away from behind you, stand in front of you, and begore you can say anything…

She opens her tiny mouth.

And a Massive Hyperbeam comes out of it.

It conects with the enemy Hyperbeam, struggles with it briefly, only for, at the amazement of everyone, as flashes about all the good and bad times start flashing around your Wooloo, your tiny sheep hyperbeam to overcome the enemy’s, pulverazing him on the spot.

Your sheep falls exahusted but happy, for she has finally saved you, and you take advantage of the Boss’ shock to grab her and run to the nearest pokemon center for shelter.

And that’s the story of how your Sheep learned Hyperbeam.
